                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_æmvars" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>æmvars</orth><form type="variant"><orth>ævvars</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ænvars</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>находящийся рядом</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>nearby</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>союзник</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>ally</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сторонник</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>supporter</q></tr></sense></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>ænværstæ næ cudæncæ, fal kæræʒemæj idærdʒæf</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>они ехали не рядом, а поодаль друг от друга</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they didn’t ride close to each other, but at a distance</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1940 III 58</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>mе ʽvvars fæci</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>он оказался на моей стороне</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he became on my side</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>ænværstæ næ cudæncæ, fal kæræʒemæj idærdʒæf</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>они ехали не рядом, а поодаль друг от друга</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they didn’t ride close to each other, but at a distance</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1940 III 58</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>mе ʽvvars fæci</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>он оказался на моей стороне</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he became on my side</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из %iæm%i + %ifars%i | %iæn%i + %ifars%i — <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*ham-parsu-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="iir"><lang/> <w>sam-paršu-</w></mentioned>; буквально „находящийся бок о бок“. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fars"/> ‘бок’ и префикс <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/>. По типу образования ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>hampušt</w> <gloss><q>помощник</q></gloss></mentioned> (%iham%i = ос. %iæm%i, %ipušt%i ‘спина’). Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævvaxs"/> ‘близкий’.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From %iæm%i + %ifars%i | %iæn%i + %ifars%i — <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>*ham-parsu-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="iir"><lang/> <w>sam-paršu-</w></mentioned>; literally “situated side by side”. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fars"/> ‘sideʼ and prefix <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/>. Concerning the derivation type, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>hampušt</w> <gloss><q>helper</q></gloss></mentioned> (%iham%i = Ossetic %iæm%i, %ipušt%i ‘back’). Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævvaxs"/> ‘nearby’.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>